This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in 2010. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of wireless broadband access in ensuring America's future competitiveness and global technology leadership. It highlights the role of the Internet as vital infrastructure and its impact on the economy. The memorandum directs executive departments, agencies, and offices to collaborate with the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) in making available a total of 500 MHz of Federal and nonfederal spectrum over the next 10 years for mobile and fixed wireless broadband use. It also calls for the development of innovative spectrum-sharing technologies and the assessment of progress in achieving the objectives outlined in the memorandum. The Department of Commerce is authorized to provide administrative support for the implementation of the memorandum.